LilyPond Procedural Melody Generator
A Python-based algorithmic composition tool that generates randomized musical scores in LilyPond format. The script uses weighted probabilities for intervals, rhythms, and rests to create unique melodies within a user-defined pitch range.

Features
Algorithmic Composition: Generates melodies based on interval steps (up/down) and weighted probabilities.

LilyPond Integration: Automatically exports sequences to a .ly file and invokes the LilyPond compiler to produce PDF/MIDI output.

Flexible Constraints: Users can define:

Time signature and number of measures.

Octave range (from sub-contra to four-line octave).

Specific pitch boundaries.

Rest/Pause probability.

Dynamic Naming: Uses the Faker library to generate unique, abstract titles for each piece.